  [Text] Beijing, June 21 KYODO -- North Korean President Kim 
Il-song said he hopes to hold a summit meeting with South Korean 
President Kim Yong-sam in North Korea in mid-August, the widow 
of former Japanese Prime Minister Takeo Miki said Tuesday. 
  Mutsuko Miki made the remarks to reporters at Beijing 
Airport 
after visiting North Korea. She met the North Korean leader 
Sunday. 

